commit_message:
Introduce a new log handler to notify exceptions and tracebacks

In common the first step to debugging a OpenStack bug always be reproduction.
But many times, logs doesn't contains enougth information, like what local
variables is, what the exception type and value is. Which make reproduction
more difficult. This blueprint introduces the first step to address this issue.

Compared with log_handler, this handler reports more detail informations
about exceptions which includes context local variables, and all frame
details.

The `publisher_id` of notification is the hostname of the real publisher,
to make notifications consumers easy to find out which host is in danger.

The `event_type` of notification is set to 'exception_notification' to
distinguish from another log_handler.

The schema of notification's payload looks like below:

    {
        "_version_": "0.1",  # The version of this payload is.
        "datetime": "2015-03-09T03:41:10.600025",
        "binary": "nova-compute",
        "hostname": "10-120-120-120",
        "exception": {
            "exc_class": "<class \'socket.error\'>",
            "exc_value": "[Errno 98] Address already in use",
            "frames": [
            {
                "filename": "/usr/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/eventlet/...",
                "local_vars": {
                    "sock": "<eventlet.greenio.GreenSocket object at ....>",
                    "family": "2",
                    "backlog": "128",
                    "addr": "(\'0.0.0.0\', 8774)"
                },
                "name": "listen",
                "context_line": "    sock.bind(addr)",
                    "addr": "(\'0.0.0.0\', 8774)"
                },
                "name": "listen",
                "context_line": "    sock.bind(addr)",
                "lineno": 38
            },
            {
                "filename": "/usr/lib/python2.7/socket.py",
                "local_vars": {
                    "self": "<socket._socketobject object at 0x7f36dccd8fa0>",
                    "args": "((\'0.0.0.0\', 8774),)",
                    "name": "\'bind\'"
                },
                "name": "meth",
                "context_line": "    return getattr(self._sock,name)(*args)",
                "lineno": 224
            }]
        }
    }

Related to blueprint consistent-exception-notifications

TODO:
  After this patch merged, using it in oslo.log like what log_handler do.

Change-Id: Ifcbbc74d78ac35ad4fec6552b2ff5b9987811229

subject: Prevent infinite loop in logging notification handlers
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-03-30 11:31:35.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_messaging/tests/test_utils.py', 'oslo_messaging/_utils.py', 'oslo_messaging/notify/logger.py', 'oslo_messaging/notify/log_handler.py'], 'message': 'Prevent infinite loop in logging notification handlers

Logging notification handlers will calling notifier to emit notifications.
when combines with log notifier, which on the contrary calls this logging
handler to do logging logic, then logging handler want to notify ......
so results in infinite looping.

To make publish_errors work with log notifier, introduce a decoration
to restrict the maximum recursion of a method. Achieve this by looking
up target method through the whole calling stack, if too much calling
happend, stop it. Also includes tests to make sure the decoration work.

The decoration also prevent bug like #1346466 resulting in infinite
error looping.

Closes-bug: #1053422
Change-Id: Iebc5243815b9b30af6aa602ff908845458c701c4
'}]
commit_message:
Prevent infinite loop in logging notification handlers

Logging notification handlers will calling notifier to emit notifications.
when combines with log notifier, which on the contrary calls this logging
handler to do logging logic, then logging handler want to notify ......
so results in infinite looping.

To make publish_errors work with log notifier, introduce a decoration
to restrict the maximum recursion of a method. Achieve this by looking
up target method through the whole calling stack, if too much calling
happend, stop it. Also includes tests to make sure the decoration work.

The decoration also prevent bug like #1346466 resulting in infinite
error looping.

Closes-bug: #1053422
Change-Id: Iebc5243815b9b30af6aa602ff908845458c701c4

commit_message:
DHCP: delete config option dnsmasq_dns_server

This field was marked as deprecated In commit
a269541c603f8923b35b7e722f1b8c0ebd42c95a. That was in Kilo
which has provided enough time for admins to addjust to this.

In addition to this the patch sets the default value as [].
If a value is not specified this is None and that should not be
the default list.

DocImpact
UpgradeImpact

Change-Id: Ieaf18ffc9baf7e1caebe9de47017338bebd92c84

commit_message:
Provide default service_name for keystone endpoint

This change updates the gnocchi::keystone::auth class to include a default
service_name of 'gnocchi' so that if a user changes the auth_name, the
service is still created as being related to 'gnocchi'.  This improves the
user experiance when they want to customize the usernames for services.

Additional changes:

* update related spec test
* add a release note
* add the service_description option in order to configure it

Change-Id: Iaca2fe1ec33041593ddc8ee9b7bd7a0cd31f1f3f
Closes-Bug: #1590040

commit_message:
Volume update API misses metadata checking

Now cinder can update user metadata by updating
volume_metadata API and updateing volume API.

But updating volume API misses the checking of
metadata properites, that will cause 500 error
if metadata value is larger than 255 characters.

Fix this bug by adding _check_metadata_properties.

Change-Id: I02286d8fe2ff77b6316d380dc932f6ecf3f7efba
Closes-Bug: #1592331

subject: Make sure we always get all limits
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-06-08 10:40:47.000000000', 'files': ['openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/instances/workflows/create_instance.py', 'openstack_dashboard/dashboards/identity/projects/tests.py', 'openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/instances/workflows/resize_instance.py', 'openstack_dashboard/dashboards/admin/overview/tests.py', 'openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/instances/tests.py', 'openstack_dashboard/test/tests/quotas.py', 'openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/overview/tests.py', 'openstack_dashboard/usage/quotas.py', 'openstack_dashboard/usage/base.py'], 'message': 'Make sure we always get all limits

When checking with nova for the absolute limits
we were not taking into account the reserved
quotas (i.e. instance in rebuilding will take
cpu and ram) so this could lead to wrongly
thinking that the user could launch more instances
that its quota allowed. It also made the overview
page display wrong quotas as it didnt took into
account those reserved resources.

Change-Id: If51470d185ddc122acbdf4cf0d0fd952f3f791a0
Closes-bug: 1561310
'}]
commit_message:
Make sure we always get all limits

When checking with nova for the absolute limits
we were not taking into account the reserved
quotas (i.e. instance in rebuilding will take
cpu and ram) so this could lead to wrongly
thinking that the user could launch more instances
that its quota allowed. It also made the overview
page display wrong quotas as it didnt took into
account those reserved resources.

Change-Id: If51470d185ddc122acbdf4cf0d0fd952f3f791a0
Closes-bug: 1561310

vm.cpu.time_ms may be reporting cpu usage in nano seconds

you should be getting what libvirt API returns which is in nano
seconds. Ref: https://libvirt.org/python.html

commit_message:
Run Python 3 unit tests in parallel

Replace testtools.run test runner with os-testr for Python 3 to run
tests in parallel.

Replace also the whitelist with a blacklist to quickly identify tests
which still must be ported to Python 3.

Blacklist backup.test_backup_models: even if it worked when run with
testtools.run, it fails when run using os-testr. We can investigate
this issue later, it's more important to reduce the duration of the
py34 job to reduce the risk of random timeout.

Add a dependency to os-testr.

Partially implements: blueprint trove-python3
Change-Id: I5ea7ebf7eec15b75a5fed07aab7bd15e5e6cd6d6

commit_message:
Use osc-lib instead of openstackclient

osc-lib is a package of common support modules for writing
OSC plugins. All common functions, classes such as exceptions,
utils, logs and so on have been moved from openstackclient to
osc-lib.

So use osc-lib instead of openstackclient in sahara client.

Change-Id: I9543988830eeeac0d09facebabdeed9a968ba3f0

commit_message:
Implement Data Sync operation

Implements the Data Sync operation, which is run using the
midonet-db-manage data-version-sync command.
config.py: removed the annotation for the config help msg.
exceptions.py: added some custome exceptions for easier handling.
data_state_db.py: added some utility functions useful for
    manipulating and testing the global data state.
data_sync_db.py: added function to perform the data sync.
cli.py: filled out cli wrapper for the data sync command.
task_db.py: create new task util functions.
test_midonet_plugin.py: add UT

Change-Id: Ice356d2c9e9972d04b24d8e95b2955b600cec69d
Partially-Implements: specs/data_sync
Signed-off-by: Joe Mills <joe@midokura.com>

commit_message:
Fix cluster next_index updating

next_index property of cluster is not updated correctly
after performing cluster-node-add operation. This is
because updated next_index value of cluster db object was
overriden by old runtime value incorrectly. This patch
tries to fix this issue.

Change-Id: Idb697049e09fc27056c91a7afa5e718132031b6b
Closes-Bug: #1595484

commit_message:
Use PRIVATE_NETWORK_NAME for devstack plugin

The devstack plugin hardcodes "private" for the default cleaning network
and when looking up the network to bind onto for IPA-conductor
communication.

Ensure we are using the devstack PRIVATE_NETWORK_NAME variable instead
of hardcoding the commonly used name.

Change-Id: I6f344edc75ad1e2ac29bd59a9804ab3cad6cf2b2
Partial-bug: #1595598

subject: Mock detector run only once for each testcase
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-06-15 21:30:13.000000000', 'files': ['trove/tests/unittests/trove_testtools.py'], 'message': 'Mock detector run only once for each testcase

The change I04d1c99df9983733b6d2579ba71097b2cebc6a54 has got
rid of the last global leaked mocks in the test code.
We can now run the mock detector only once after each test class.

Aside from reducing the job runtime this also has an additional
benefit of being able to detect global mock references that
could not be caught before because they exist both before and after
the test run and hence do not show up in the difference.

Change-Id: Ib0c471ce2e1397055744bdb200f9b56183dd2d5a
'}]
commit_message:
Mock detector run only once for each testcase

The change I04d1c99df9983733b6d2579ba71097b2cebc6a54 has got
rid of the last global leaked mocks in the test code.
We can now run the mock detector only once after each test class.

Aside from reducing the job runtime this also has an additional
benefit of being able to detect global mock references that
could not be caught before because they exist both before and after
the test run and hence do not show up in the difference.

Change-Id: Ib0c471ce2e1397055744bdb200f9b56183dd2d5a

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-06-10 15:57:56.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/resource/core.py'], 'message': 'exception sensitive cache/audit changes

Several places were doing things between when a cached resource was
changed and when the cache was invalidated, which could lead to
problems, e.g. if the code in between the two raised an exception,
or if an audit event resulted in the resource being requeried before
the cache was invalidated. Review comments on the original patch also
pointed out that audit events would not be sent in some exeption cases.

This change does cache invalidation as quickly as possible after a
change and uses try/finally logic to ensure that audit events will
be sent even in exception cases.

It also removes a stale TODO and an unnecessary duplicate assignment
removal in the affected code.

Change-Id: If9a91da42818fe37c975f86be47a2e49da356e41
'}]
commit_message:
exception sensitive cache/audit changes

Several places were doing things between when a cached resource was
changed and when the cache was invalidated, which could lead to
problems, e.g. if the code in between the two raised an exception,
or if an audit event resulted in the resource being requeried before
the cache was invalidated. Review comments on the original patch also
pointed out that audit events would not be sent in some exeption cases.

This change does cache invalidation as quickly as possible after a
change and uses try/finally logic to ensure that audit events will
be sent even in exception cases.

It also removes a stale TODO and an unnecessary duplicate assignment
removal in the affected code.

Change-Id: If9a91da42818fe37c975f86be47a2e49da356e41

commit_message:
EntityTemplate has no property of parent_type

EntityTemplate is the parent of NodeTemplate, but there is no definition
of parent_type, so the method of is_derived_from will be error
when call the parent_type's method.

commit_message:
OVS: don't throw KeyError when duplicate VLAN tags exist

In _restore_local_vlan_map() we can have two ports with the
same VLAN tag, but trying to remove the second will throw
a KeyError, causing the agent to not start.  Use discard()
instead so we only remove an entry if it's there.

Closes-bug: #1526974
Change-Id: I479c693f490c704c5b6c1462e9ab236684e9c259
(cherry picked from commit d2508163cfcede20df641239be081fe63c79150b)

commit_message:
[install] include "get started with.." content in chapters

Including the "get started with.." subchapters into the starting page of
a chpater helps to reduce text duplication and helps to remove the
double redundant titles (e.g. title of the chapter is "Block Storage
service" and the title of the first subchapter is "OpenStack Block
Storage").

Change-Id: Id8ac2d3a6bf8848bc490a44097ff6e4e2eb90836

commit_message:
Update to use setuptools_scm for release version generation

To support openstack-infra we store the release version in git
tags and use setuptools_scm to extract that tag in the setup
file when generating sdist and wheel files.

This patch includes the use of the new xstatic-release tool
which handles the majority of management of metadata to support
the infra release process.

Change-Id: I14e0b5986d3433afd796ea44e66dfafd5003e732

commit_message:
fix wrong id for render default config param 'server_id'

built_in 'id' will cause trove configuration_default call
return the same 'server_id', user may put the 'server_id'
to a configuration group and attach later. finally, this
may cause mysql replication failed. use instance id instead.

Change-Id: Iebd409daf40e092a65641d2bc24899c90bdc18fe
Closes-bug: #1592225

commit_message:
Move the rabbit/rpc options to its own section

Using the DEFAULT section for rabbit configuration is deprecated, so
all rabbit related option should be moved to the oslo_messaging_rabbit
section. The example agent config still respects the
TROVE_HOST_GATEWAY option.

This change has to depend on a change in redstack that otherwise
overwrites the hard work we do here :)

commit_message:
add "needs:*" tags to the config option modules

To make it trackable which fixes the config options need, we add tag
at the beginning of the files. If the fix is done, the tag will be
removed. We discussed this on the ML with [1].

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-May/095538.html

Implements blueprint centralize-config-options-newton

Change-Id: Ibcd89bc550c6f534b5fa297df74bd59eb481e921
